 important medium for community communication as the recent rise of the <a href=\"!elink-en-wikipedia-org\">podcast phenomenon</a> demonstrates.','6.9'),(3641,' audio.module:13','default','Users create audio nodes by uploading a file from their computer. They are then able to make changes to the metadata, perhaps adding an artist, or removing the track number. Visitors can download the audio file, view the file\'s metadata and encoding information, or browse for audio by metadata (artist, title, year, etc). Visitors can even play MP3s within their browser using the <a href=\"!elink-musicplayer-sourceforge-net\">XSPF flash player</a> that is bundled with the module.','6.9'),(3642,' audio.module:14','default','The module uses the <a href=\"!elink-www-getid3-org\">getID3 library</a> to read and write <a href=\"%elink-en-wikipedia-org\">ID3 tag</a> information from the audio file. getID3 can read metadata from a many different audio and video formats giving the audio module a great deal of flexibility.','6.9'),(3643,' audio.module:15','default','<p>You can:</p>\n                    <ul>\n                    <li>add an audio file at <a href=\"!node-add-audio\">create content &gt;&gt; audio</a>.</li>\n                    <li>see your most recent audio files at <a href=\"!user\">user account</a>.</li>\n                    <li>see all of the most recently added audio files at <a href=\"!audio\">audio</a>.</li>\n                    <li>browse for audio by its metadata (artist, album, genre, etc) at <a href=\"!audio-by\">audio &gt;&gt; by</a>.</li>\n                    <li>enable the <em>latest audio</em>, <em>random audio</em>, and <em>browse for audio</em> blocks at <a href=\"!admin-build-block\">administer &gt;&gt; build &gt;&gt; block</a>.</li>\n                    <li>administer audio module at <a href=\"!admin-settings-audio\">administer &gt;&gt; site configuration &gt;&gt; audio</a>.</li>\n                    </ul>','6.9'),(3644,' audio.module:24','default','For more i